# Pagination — React

Package: `@acko/pagination`
Directive: `"use client"` (interactive)

## Props Interface

```typescript
interface PaginationProps {
  totalPages: number;
  currentPage: number;
  onPageChange: (page: number) => void;
  variant?: 'numbered' | 'simple' | 'compact' | 'load-more';
  siblingCount?: number;
  showInfo?: boolean;
  className?: string;
}
```

## Icons

Pagination navigates to a new page (state change), so it uses **arrow** icons — not chevrons. See `foundation/iconography.mdc`.

- Previous: `ArrowLeftIcon` (inline SVG, 20×20)
- Next: `ArrowRightIcon` (inline SVG, 20×20)

## Accessibility

- `<nav aria-label="Pagination">`
- Current page: `aria-current="page"`
- Disabled buttons: `aria-disabled="true"`
- Prev/Next: `aria-label="Previous page"` / `aria-label="Next page"`

## Exports

```typescript
export { Pagination } from './Pagination';
export type { PaginationProps } from './Pagination';
```
